-- Kaupthing to Enter Composition Agreement by June, Visir Says
-- B y   O m a r   R .   V a l d i m a r s s o n
-- 2011-12-29T11:05:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/kaupthing-to-enter-composition-agreement-by-june-visir-says.html
The Winding-Up Committee of failed
Icelandic lender  Kaupthing Bank hf (KAUP)  is planning to seek a
composition agreement with its creditors by the end of the
second quarter of 2012, Visir reported, citing documents from
the bank.  Should the composition accord be approved Kaupthing will be
transformed into a holding company, owned and operated by its
creditors, the Reykjavik-based  online news site  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Omar R. Valdimarsson in Reykjavik 
